Inter-Party Advisory Council, IPAC, Katsina State chapter has warned the PDP chairman, Alhaji Salisu Majigiri not to meddle in the affairs of the party, describing him as an impostor. The state IPAC chairman, Alhaji Ibrahim Tukur Saude gave the warning while addressing newsmen on the crisis bedevilling the state chapter of the PDP in Katsina on Monday. The chairman who noted that there was a court judgement that sacked the entire executives of the party in Katsina state from the state to the ward level, said Majigiri led executive has no right whatsoever to threaten party followers of any suspension. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He therefore advised the national leadership of the PDP to urgently constitute a caretaker committee to run the affairs of the party at all levels in Katsina state. “Going by the security challenges faced by the state it is not proper to allow the Majigiri faction of the PDP to compound it’s problems through unnecessary decisive crisis”, he said. S’Africa Passes 30,000 Confirmed COVID-19 Deaths, With 434 In Just One Day Ekene Dili Chukwu’s Son Dies Of COVID-19 In Lagos Saude also called on the security agencies in the state to urgently arrest any person parading himself as PDP executives in the state, stressing that, a court judgment had put paid to the existence of such in the state. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION